<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,537,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diphascon (Adropion) scoticum</emphasis>
Murray 
<number box="[651,710,1631,1657]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1902.0">1902</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1631,2018]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
I collected 
<specimenCount box="[334,495,1672,1698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">
<number box="[334,363,1672,1698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="78.0">78</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
from LF samples. No drop present between the buccal and pharyngeal tubes. Three rod-shaped macroplacoids, microplacoid and septulum (as specimens studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramazzotti" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Ramazzotti, G. &amp; Maucci, W. (1983) Il phylum Tardigrada. III edizione riveduta e aggiornata. Memorie dell'Istituto Italiano di Idrobiologia Dott. Marco de Marchi, 41, 1 - 1012." type="journal article" year="1983">
Ramazzotti and Maucci (
<number box="[255,315,1752,1778]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1983.0">1983</number>
))
</bibRefCitation>
within the pharyngeal bulb, but I observed one specimen lacking the septulum in the pharyngeal bulb as 
<bibRefCitation author="Pilato" box="[297,450,1792,1818]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Pilato, G. (1974) Studio su Diphascon scoticum J. Murr., 1905 (Eutardigrada) e alcune altre specie ritenute ad esso affine. Animalia, 1, 73 - 88." type="journal article" year="1974">
Pilato (
<number box="[381,442,1792,1818]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1974.0">1974</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ito" box="[507,625,1792,1818]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Ito, M. (1995) Taxonomic study on the Eutardigrada from the Northern slope of Mt. Fuji, Central Japan. II. Family Hypsibiidae. Proceedings of the Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, 53, 18 - 39." type="journal article" year="1995">
Ito (
<number box="[555,616,1792,1818]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did for this species. Cuticle bars, when present, appeared in the inner zone of the internal double-claws and/or between external and internal double-claw of the first three pairs of legs. Mean body size was 
<number box="[460,504,1872,1898]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="754.0">754</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[613,661,1872,1898]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="254.0">254</number>
), range 
<number box="[755,896,1872,1898]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="957.0" valueMax="1496.0" valueMin="418.0">418 to 1496</number>
μm. This species is considered cosmopolitan. In the Iberian Peninsula, it has been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[727,794,1912,1938]" name="Spain" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez" box="[808,1069,1912,1938]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Rodriguez Roda, J. (1946) Contribucion al estudio de los Tardigrados de Espana. Nota previa sobre los de Aralar. In: R. Margalef, ed. Aportacion al estudio de la fauna y flora vasco-Navarra, Sierra de Aralar. CSIC. Estacion de estudios Pirenaicos, 67 - 82." type="book chapter" year="1946">
Rodríguez Roda 
<number box="[1008,1069,1912,1938]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1946.1952">1946</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Roda" box="[1082,1144,1912,1938]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Rodriguez Roda, J. (1952) Tardigrados de la Fauna Espanola. Doctoral Thesis. Trabajos del Museo de Ciencias Naturales de Barcelona, Nueva serie Zoologica, 1 (4), 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="1952">1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maucci" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Maucci, W. &amp; Durante Pasa, V. (1984) Macrobiotus lusitanicus sp. nov. nuova specie di eutardigrado del portogallo nord - occidentale. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 11, 319 - 326." type="journal article" year="1984">
Maucci &amp; Durante Pasa 
<number box="[151,214,1952,1978]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is the first record for Madrid (
<tableCitation box="[605,695,1952,1978]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1706,1730]" captionTargetBox="[159,1400,1802,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2. Tardigrada species found in the Sierra de Guadarrama. New records (NR) for Europe (Eur), the Iberian Peninsula (IbPn), Spain (Spn) and Madrid Province (Mad) are indicated." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" tableUuid="DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C">
Table 
<number box="[678,695,1952,1978]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2.0">2</number>
</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[717,1091,1952,1977]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Diphascon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="scoticum" subGenus="Adropion">
<emphasis box="[717,1091,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diphascon (Adropion) scoticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in 
<number box="[1292,1321,1952,1978]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="17.0">17</number>
sampling points (Table 
<number box="[311,328,1992,2018]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
